Wendell High School
20 hrs ·

Tonight the Wendell Trojans hosted the Cole Valley Christian Chargers. The Chargers won the game 58 to 0. Here are the stats for the game.

Offense:

Joey Ward completed 8 passes for 84 yards and ran the ball 15 times for 62 yards.

Aden Bunn caught 2 passes for 52 yards.

Jaxson Kelly caught one pass for 11 yards.

Teegan Dunn ran the ball 21 times for 41 yards.

Defense:

Aden Bunn lead the way for the Trojans with 15 tackles.

Teegan Dunn and Clayton Hester each had 5 tackles and Hester had two of those tackles for a loss.

Wendell High School
September 9 at 8:24 PM ·

Today the Lady Trojans traveled to Filer to play on the Lady Wildcats. In the first half, goals were scored by Yadira Alvarez Guzman, three goals, a hat trick. Ali Orozco also scored a goal. Assist by Yoselin Acevedo another assist by Lorena Madera. At half the score was 4-0 Wendell. In the second half, Ali Orozco scored another goal with an assist by Jackeline Alvarez. Filer scored a goal with 10 minutes left. The Lady Trojans played great by moving the ball and connecting their passes. Final score Wendell 5-Filer 1. The Lady Trojans play against Community School at home on Monday, September 14th at 5:30 pm. Come support the ladies.

shared_text:
Wendell Elementary School-Idaho
September 3 at 9:43 AM ·

Thank you so much for the very generous gift of water bottles for our students to use at school. As a safety measure we shut off our hallway water fountains and students have a water bottle we fill up throughout the school day. We are two weeks into the school year and this has worked well because of your donation to us.

Wendell Elementary sure appreciates working with you, a local business. Our students know you gave them this water and together we are making a safe school for Wendell students to attend.

The Staff and Students of Wendell Elementary School

shared_text:
Wendell High School
August 18 at 1:21 PM ·

Due to COVID we were unable to celebrate our 2019-20 Classified and Certified staff members of the year. We recognized them today during the HS staff meeting! HS staff members voted on these awards. 🙂

Kelli Jasper is our Certified staff member of the year! Mrs. Jasper wears many hats at the HS and is alway looking out for the students best interest. Seniors projects, volleyball, and Special Education are some of the great things she does at the HS. Kelli Mattix Jasper

Marilyn Davidson is our classified staff member of the year. She also retired this year after 17 years of service in the WSD. Marilyn ran a tight ship at the HS and her knowledge of the school and building will be greatly missed. Enjoy your retirement MD!! We will miss you dearly.

Congratulations to you both again. Fantastic employees in the WSD. :)

shared_text:
Wendell Elementary School-Idaho
August 11 at 11:38 AM ·

Leap into Kindergarten!!
Kindergarten is going to look a little different this year. The 1st week of school, August 24th-27th each Kindergartener will only come to school for one day. This will give the Kindergarten teachers a chance to get to know each child, introduce them to the school, and be able to do their screener. The Kindergarten teachers will work together and have every child placed into their classroom by Friday the 28th. Each parent will be notified by that day what teacher they will have for the school year. Then on August 31st Kindergarteners will begin with a regular schedule.

My child __________________________ will come to school on:

August 24 August 25 August 26 August 27

August 31: 1st full week of Kindergarten

Wendell Middle School
August 7 at 10:45 AM ·

Reminder that we have registration starting August 10 – 12; 9:30 am to 12:30 pm and 3:30 – 6:30 pm. This is for all students attending middle school. Face Masks are required. We ask, when you come to register, that it is only 1 parent/guardian and 1 child. You will need to bring 2 forms of proof of residency, if you pre-registered in May; you are not required to bring the proof of residency. We accept cash, check and credit cards for payment of school fees.

Good news, yearbooks have arrived; you can pick them up during registration. We have extras if you are interested in getting one. We look forward to seeing you next week.

post_text:
Hi Folks

I wanted to inform you last week the school board adopted the attached school and activity guidelines for reopening our buildings in August. I'd highly suggest you read through them.

Our administration, supervisors, and WEA are meeting next week to finalize/discuss details of the guidelines. We are ALL excited to have our children back in our schools!

We have purchased masks and face shields for all staff. We will provide hand sanitizer throughout all facilities. Our custodians will continue to deep clean and disinfect the buildings. Safety will be a priority!

Thanks for all you do. WE ARE GOING TO GET THROUGH THIS PANDEMIC TOGETHER. We are Wendell "tuff" and it's going to be a great year! Please let me know if you have any questions or concerns.

Go Trojans,

Tim

--
Tim Perrigot, Ed. D

https://www.sde.idaho.gov/re-opening/files/Idaho-Back-to-School-Framework-2020.pdf

Wendell Elementary School-Idaho
July 17 at 5:12 PM ·

Wendell Elementary School
Kindergarten Suggested Supply List
2020-2021
Pencil box/ Caja de lapices
Pencils/Lapices
Scissors (that cut well)/Tijeras (que cortan bien)
Boxes of Crayons/Caja de crayolas
Backpack ( one that is large enough to hold papers and folders)/Mochila (grande para detener los papeles y folders)
Box of tissues/ Caja de Kleenex
Cleaning Wipes/Toallitas de limpieza
Markers/Marcadores
Water Color Paints/Pinturas de Acuarelas
$6 donation for Weekly Reader/Donación de $ 6 para el lector semanal

Please label your child's backpack, pencil box, lunches, and scissors. Etiquete la mochila, la caja de lápices, los almuerzos y las tijeras de su hijo.
Your child should be able to dress themselves as well as put shoes on and off. If they can not tie shoes or do the button on their pants, please consider easier options.
Su hijo debe poder vestirse solo y ponerse y quitarse los zapatos. Si no pueden atar los zapatos o abrocharse los pantalones, considere opciones más fáciles

Wendell School District is seeking to hire a Transportation Supervisor for the 2020-2021 school year. Applicant needs to have a high school diploma and training or experience in repair and maintenance of automotive equipment: or any equivalent combination of training and experience which provides the required skills, knowledge and abilities. Applicant needs to possess a valid Class B Commercial Driver's License with a passenger and air brake endorsement required for mechanics. This position includes benefits. Applications are available on the district website:
www.wendellschools.org and position is open until filled.

Parent Request for Classroom Teacher.
If a parent feels it is necessary to request a teacher for their student next year this is the process: email school principal at pchapman@wendellschools.org with your student's full name, current grade level, teacher your requesting and why you are requesting this teacher for your student next year. All teacher requests are due May 11 and must be in writing. Thank you./Solicitud de los padres para el maestro de aula.
Si un padre siente que es necesario solicitar un maestro para su estudiante el próximo año, este es el proceso: envíe un correo electrónico al director de la escuela a pchapman@wendellschools.org con el nombre completo de su estudiante, el grado actual, el maestro que solicita y por qué está solicitando este maestro para tu estudiante el año que viene. Todas las solicitudes de maestros deben presentarse el 11 de mayo y deben presentarse por escrito. Gracias.

April 27 at 12:31 PM ·

Students currently in 8th, 9th, 10th, and 11th grade: Please don't forget to register for next year's classes on PowerSchool. If you register this week, you may pick up your schedule in 2 weeks.
How to register:
1. Log into PS and click on "Class Registration" on the left side of the screen
2. Find the red exclamation points and click on one of them.
3. Follow the directions and choose the number of classes that is indicated.
4. Once all the red exclamation marks have turned green, you are finished.
If you have questions, feel free to email Ms. Webberley

Wendell High School
April 12 at 7:15 PM ·

**Current Grades- 8th, 9th, 10th & 11th**

Students---It's time to choose your electives for the 2020-21 school year. Here's how to do it:
1. Log onto PowerSchool.
2. Choose "Class Registration" on the left side of the screen.
3. Find the red exclamation points and click on the boxes.
4. Choose your electives and alternate electives and don't forget to hit "submit" once all red exclamation points are gone.

During TAG recently, we learned about the different electives offered here at WHS. Choose the ones that interest you or that might be good to take as preparation for your chosen educational path and career. If you have any questions, feel free to email Ms. Webberley at twebberley@wendellschools.org. Please complete as soon as possible!

Thanks to KMVT for this information.

ACADEMIC ALL-STAR - Wendell Trojan Neida Romo!!
Neida maintains a 4.0 GPA, is a member of National Honor Society, and is Senior Class Secretary.

She has volunteered and donated at 2 blood drives and also volunteers at school concessions, senior breakfast and the soup kitchen.

Neida completed a field day in the elementary school and is a Spanish translator in math class. She has been actively involved for multiple years in Drama/Theater, band and pep band.

Neida competed in the Quiz Bowl, and she has been awarded the Presidential Award for two years. She is a member of the prom committee and won prom princess her junior year.

She plans to major in Business Administration at Washington State University.

Congratulations Neida, this week's First Federal Academic All Star!!

Idaho’s May 19th primary election won’t be delayed, but will go all-absentee due to the risk of Covid-19.
What should you watch for?
1. A mass mailing from the Secretary of State outlining the timeline and what you need to do.
2. Watch your mail for your ballot, which you will mail back.
This election will include the renewal of our Supplemental Levy. Remember, this is a renewal and will NOT raise your taxes. You can also still request an absentee ballot from the Gooding County Clerk’s Office if you wish.

PLAN para WHS
Estudiantes y padres -
El personal de WHS trabajará toda esta semana en preparación para el aprendizaje remoto y distante que comenzará oficialmente el lunes 6 de abril. Sin embargo, este jueves los maestros de TAG de sus estudiantes llamarán a casa para hacer algunas preguntas de una encuesta. Las respuestas a estas preguntas son cruciales para darnos una mejor comprensión de cómo apoyarlo a usted y a su familia durante el cierre de la escuela por el COVID-19.

¿Qué se puede hacer mientras tanto? Asegúrese de que la computadora portátil de sus estudiantes esté en funcionamiento y lista para ir entrar a Google Classroom, que será nuestra principal plataforma educativa. ¿No tienes internet? Por favor, avísele al maestro de TAG el jueves y tendremos otro plan para apoyar a todos.

Si tiene alguna pregunta, comuníquese con el Director Alsterlund en Facebook o jalsterlund@wendellschools.org

El personal de WHS trabajará toda esta semana en preparación para el aprendizaje remoto y distante que comenzará oficialmente el lunes 6 de abril. Sin embargo, este jueves los maestros de TAG de sus estudiantes llamarán a casa para hacer algunas preguntas de una encuesta. Las respuestas a estas preguntas son cruciales para darnos una mejor comprensión de cómo apoyarlo a usted y a su familia durante el cierre de la escuela por el COVID-19.

¿Qué se puede hacer mientras tanto? Asegúrese de que la computadora portátil de sus estudiantes esté en funcionamiento y lista para ir entrar a Google Classroom, que será nuestra principal plataforma educativa. ¿No tienes internet? Por favor, avísele al maestro de TAG el jueves y tendremos otro plan para apoyar a todos.

Si tiene alguna pregunta, comuníquese con el Director Alsterlund en Facebook o jalsterlund@wendellschools.org

Las conferencias de padres y maestros son esta semana el miércoles y jueves de 4:30 a 8:00. Los estudiantes que asisten a un de los 2 días con sus padres o tutores obtendrán lo siguiente.

- Puntos adicionales en cada clase.
- 1 día de falta injustificadas se le quitara a su faltas.
- Sus padres entraran a una rifa de $100.00 en efectivo.
- Los estudiantes serán entrados a una rifa $50.00 en efectivo.

post_text: The Wendell Middle School/High School Music Department is cordially inviting you to join us on February 15th for a Night of Music Dinner and Show in the Wendell High School Commons. Small group performances will feature the WHS and WMS students as well as a special performance from Mosaic Jazz from Twin Falls. Spaghetti dinner will be served from 6-9 p.m. and there will also be games for the kids. Tickets prices are $20.00 for a family or $5.00 per person and are available from any band member or from Mr. McCarty at the high school. Please come and support our local musicians doing what they do best - making music!

post_text: Our District Maintenance Supervisor, Troy Fletcher, was awarded the "Wrench of the Year" award from Idaho Power for outstanding energy saving initiative he has implemented throughout Wendell School District. Troy was nominated by Idaho Power Employee, Leo Sanchez and was chosen from nominees from Idaho, Oregon and Washington. Thanks, Troy, for always being willing to better our district!
text: Our District Maintenance Supervisor, Troy Fletcher, was awarded the "Wrench of the Year" award from Idaho Power for outstanding energy saving initiative he has implemented throughout Wendell School District. Troy was nominated by Idaho Power Employee, Leo Sanchez and was chosen from nominees from Idaho, Oregon and Washington. Thanks, Troy, for always being willing to better our district!

post_text: Idaho Power representatives came to the School Board meeting on November 19th to present the district with a check for $16,983.88. This check represents the amount of money the district has save over the past year through energy saving programs the district has been following. A special thank you to all staff for participating!
